-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/keidanren-says-pay-disclosure-won-t-improve-governance-nikkei-reports.html

          
          
             Hiromasa Yonekura, chairman of
Sumitomo Chemical Co. and the new chairman of the Japan Business
Federation, or Nippon Keidanren, criticized a new requirement
that companies disclose executive pay over 100 million yen
($1.11 million), Nikkei English News reported.  
 He said pay disclosure rules in the U.S. had done little to
corral compensation or improve governance, and said Japanâ€™s
threshold should be higher, Nikkei reported.  
          
          


  


        